Kano state governor, Dr. Abdullahi Umar Ganduje has taken a drastic action against the state Commissioner of Works Engineer Mu’azu Magaji for his negative comments over the death of Chief of Staff to the President Malam Abba Kyari who died yesterday in Lagos. The position of the governor which is expected to be carried out expeditiously described such snarky and nasty comments as uncalled-for given the position of a Commissioner who is holding sensitive position in government. A statement signed by the commissioner for Information, Malam Muhammad Garba said the commissioner was removed following his unguarded utterances against the person of the late Chief of Staff to the President, Malam Abba Kyari. He said as a public servant, the commissioner ought to have respect the profanity of the office by refraining from any act capable of rendering the office to disrepute. The action of a public servant, personal or otherwise reflects back on the government and therefore, the Ganduje administration would not tolerate people in official capacities engaging in personal vendetta or otherwise. According to the statement, late Abba Kyari had led a life worthy of emulation by serving his country to the best of his ability.